    and you'll hear a tale ¶

00:05.471 --> 00:07.439
¶ A tale of a fateful trip ¶

00:07.508 --> 00:09.808
¶ That started
    from this tropic port ¶

00:09.876 --> 00:12.177
¶ Aboard this tiny ship ¶

00:12.246 --> 00:14.512
¶ The mate was
     a mighty sailin' man ¶

00:14.581 --> 00:16.681
¶ The Skipper brave and sure ¶

00:16.750 --> 00:19.218
¶ Five passengers
      set sail that day ¶

00:19.286 --> 00:21.453
¶ For a three hour tour ¶

00:21.522 --> 00:25.223
¶ A three hour tour ¶

00:25.292 --> 00:27.492
[thunder rumbling]

00:27.561 --> 00:29.461
¶ The weather started
     getting rough ¶

00:29.530 --> 00:31.463
¶ The tiny ship was tossed ¶

00:31.531 --> 00:34.299
¶ If not for the courage
    of the fearless crew ¶

00:34.368 --> 00:36.568
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:36.637 --> 00:38.503
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

